<%= section_header('Hana') %>
<div class="wrapper medium-minor">
  <p class="medium">
    Hana is a small town located on the east side of Maui. It is home to some of the world’s most beautiful beaches, breath taking waterfalls, and majestic coastlines. From Kahului airport it is about a 50 mile drive along the winding coastline. Along the way you can enjoy hiking trails, beautiful overlooks, and incredible waterfalls. The actual town of Hana is very small, consisting on two convenience stores, the Travasa Hotel, Hana Ranch Restaurant, Post office, and a gas station. There are a variety of outdoor activities, some of which we’ve listed below. It is nice to have a couple of days to spend in Hana because it is a long trip out here. That way you have some time to just relax and explore this side of the island.
  </p>
  <p>
    For more information on Hana please visit <a target="_blank" href="http://www.hanamaui.com">hanamaui.com</a>
  </p>
  <h4>Activities</h4>
  <ul class="pad">
    <li>Go hang gliding down the road (1 minute away):
      <a target="_blank" href="http://www.hangglidingmaui.com">hangglidingmaui.com</a></li>
    <li>Spelunking in lava tube (2 minutes away): <a target="_blank" href="http://www.mauicave.com">mauicave.com</a>
    </li>
    <li>Go kayaking, snorkeling, surfing, or free diving (10 minutes away):
      <a target="_blank" href="http://www.hanabaykayaks.com">hanabaykayaks.com</a></li>
    <li>Guided hike and taro patch tour at Kapahu Living Farm (45 minutes away):
      <a target="_blank" href="http://kipahulu.org/hike.html">kipahulu.org/hike.html</a></li>
    <li>Ohe’o (7 Sacred Pools) and bamboo forest (45 minutes away):
      <a target="_blank" href="http://www.nps.gov/hale/index.htm">nps.gov/hale/</a></li>
    <li>Horse back riding (45 minutes away): <a target="_blank" href="http://www.mauistables.com">mauistables.com</a></li>
  </ul>
